---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Georgia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/georgia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Turkey for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/turkey' },
  { title: 'Montenegro for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/montenegro' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/portugal' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'georgiaFit', header: 'Georgia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'GEL$690-985/mo', georgiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'GEL$805-1,150/mo', georgiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'GEL$620-885/mo', georgiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'GEL$575-820/mo', georgiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', entryAge: '69', renewal: 'To 69', monthlyFrom: 'GEL$230-380/mo', georgiaFit: 'Budget' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'GEL$620-985', annual: 'GEL$7,440-11,820' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'GEL$850-1,315', annual: 'GEL$10,200-15,780' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'GEL$1,145-1,765', annual: 'GEL$13,740-21,180' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'GEL$50-150/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'GEL$200-600/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Georgia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Georgia. Ancient culture, wine country, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Georgia"
  subheadline="Georgia offers ancient culture, stunning mountains, legendary hospitality, affordable living, and 1-year visa-free for many nationalities—an emerging retirement gem at Eurasia's crossroads."
  heroImage="/images/countries/georgia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Georgia</h2>
  <p>
    Georgia offers ancient culture, world-class wine regions, dramatic Caucasus mountains, legendary hospitality, and remarkably affordable living. The 1-year visa-free entry for 95+ countries makes it exceptionally accessible. For adventurous retirees seeking value and culture, Georgia delivers.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tbilisi offers capital city with modern healthcare and historic charm. Batumi on Black Sea coast has subtropical climate. Kutaisi provides cultural center in west. Wine regions (Kakheti) attract oenophiles. Mountain areas offer dramatic scenery but limited healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; good private options in Tbilisi</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Georgian; Russian; English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> GEL$2,500-5,000/month (~$900-1,850 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Varied; continental in east; subtropical coast</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Hospitable; traditional; emerging</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> 1-year visa-free for 95+ countries</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Georgia Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Georgia healthcare is improving rapidly—private hospitals in Tbilisi offer good quality. Evex Hospitals, Aversi Clinic, and National Center of Surgery are leading facilities. Quality has improved significantly in recent years with modern equipment and trained doctors.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare exists but private preferred. Costs are very affordable even without insurance. Complex cases may require evacuation to Turkey or Europe. Tbilisi has best healthcare; rural areas limited. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Improving Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Georgia healthcare has improved significantly. Private hospitals in Tbilisi are good for most conditions. Very affordable even self-pay. Complex conditions may need Turkey (Istanbul 2 hours) or Europe. International insurance provides security and evacuation coverage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Georgia has exceptionally open visa policy:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry (1 Year)</h3>
  <p>
    Citizens of 95+ countries can stay 1 year without visa. Simply exit and re-enter for another year. No minimum stay outside required. Remarkably easy for long-term stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For those wanting formal residence. Investment, property, employment, or pension pathways. Renewable; can lead to permanent residence.
  </p>

  <h3>Remote Work/Remotely from Georgia</h3>
  <p>
    Digital nomad-friendly; no formal program needed due to visa-free access. Popular with remote workers and retirees alike.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Georgia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> No insurance required for visa-free entry</li>
    <li><strong>Residence permit:</strong> May require health insurance proof</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Affordable care:</strong> Self-pay viable but insurance provides security</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Georgia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance recommended despite affordable local care. Provides evacuation to Turkey/Europe for complex conditions. Local costs so low that high-deductible international plans work well. Combine affordable local care with international backup.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Georgia, international coverage with evacuation recommended:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Georgia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Worldwide coverage, strong network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>SafetyWing:</strong> Budget option for younger seniors</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Works well with affordable local care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage options for Georgia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Georgia (GEL ~2.7 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care so affordable; save on premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Self-pay routine:</strong> Doctor visits ~$30-50; use insurance for major</li>
    <li><strong>Tbilisi base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>Regional evacuation:</strong> Turkey provides backup</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Explorer, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Visa-free entry. Tbilisi.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with $2,500 deductible. Self-pay routine care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~GEL$750/month. Adventurous retirement; excellent value.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: German Wine Enthusiast, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,200/month pension. 1-year visa-free. Kakheti wine region.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Europe coverage. Return to Germany for complex care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~GEL$950/month. Wine country living; European backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Budget Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,800/month pension. Visa-free. Batumi.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with high deductible. Local care for routine.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~GEL$700/month. Coastal living; stretch pension further.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I really stay 1 year visa-free?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—citizens of 95+ countries including US, UK, EU, Canada, Australia can stay 365 days without visa. Exit briefly and re-enter for another year. No minimum stay outside. Remarkably easy for long-term stays without formal immigration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Georgia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of safest countries in region. Low violent crime. Tbilisi safe for walking at night. Avoid conflict zones (Abkhazia, South Ossetia). Hospitality culture is genuine. Generally welcoming to foreigners.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to speak Georgian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but English growing—younger Georgians often speak English. Russian still common from Soviet era. Google Translate helps. Tbilisi more English-friendly than rural areas. Learning basic Georgian appreciated.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Georgia really that affordable?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—among Europe's most affordable. $1,000-1,500/month covers comfortable living in Tbilisi. Rent $300-600 for nice apartment. Meals $5-15. Wine extremely affordable. Healthcare costs fraction of Western prices. Genuine value.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Georgia coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Georgian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
